Pika-KILL

- Was taken into foundation custody after reports of BRVR murdering a animal Horder.

- Dried blood, claw marks, and glow-in-the-dark stickers cover his walls.

- Hates Sonic. EXE.

- Will put his mouth on anything, especially if it looks edible and colorful.

- Likes Loneliness.

- Has shocked people to death.

- Tries to hunt Mr. Widemouth.

- Speaks using his speech boxes that appear out of nowhere.

blog.name: weirdandwackypokefusions

blog.description:
Welcome!  I create, using the all-mighty classic Microsoft XP Paint, my own pokemon fusions. All the sprites come from pokestadium and usually people on deviantart/ the xy/sun&moon sprite project. I don't own any of the sprite used, I just fuse them! 
REQUESTS ARE OPEN! Ask Box: 3/15.
PLEASE FEEL FREE TO DRAW MY FUSIONS!!  I absolutely love it when people draw them! There's no need to ask either! Just make sure you tag me so them I can see it!
I hope you enjoy my fusions!

caption:
Rapcanitails

Rapidash, Arcanine and Ninetails

Fire Type

Ability: Flame Body/Drought

Hidden Ability: Intimidate

Stats: HP - 85, Atk - 115, Def - 85, SpA - 100, SpD - 90, Spe - 115

The Legendary Flame Pokemon

This pokefusion’s fire burns forever and, even when splashed with water, will continue to burn until death.  It’s presence can bring great power to anyone who gazes upon it. When it runs at top speed (150 mph), it is very difficult to see with the naked eye.

Request for @the-dragonwolf-den.  I hope you like it. I really like this one.  Good pupper.

summary: Left Image: Bonus book cover from February 2003 Shogaku Gonensei Magazine (Grade 5 Magazine). Right Image: Autograph board at an...
caption:
Left Image: Bonus book cover from February 2003 Shogaku Gonensei Magazine (Grade 5 Magazine).

Right Image: Autograph board at an author’s signing at the New Generation World Hobby Fair.

Satoshi Yamamoto (Manga Artist) said:

The characters drawn in the early part of the chapter (RS arc) look unsettled, and seeing them is kind of embarrassing. 

Hidenori Kusaka (Story Scenario Writer) said: 

I was so excited when I saw the finalized autograph boards. Every day I was desperately trying to make the fourth chapter (RS arc) more exciting…!

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.
